comments: Gobert (UTA) sets the screen on Ingram (NOP) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Mitchell (UTA) maintains legal guarding position on Holiday (NOP) on the perimeter.
Mitchell (UTA) makes incidental contact with Holiday (NOP) during his drive that does not cause him to lose his balance.
Gobert (UTA) moves into Favors' (NOP) path and initiates the marginal contact.
Gobert (UTA) grabs Ball's (NOP) arm and affects his SQBR after the steal.
Redick (NOP) sets the screen on Conley (UTA) and does not deliver contact.
Mitchell (UTA) reaches in and makes contact with the ball and any ensuing contact with Ball (NOP) is incidental.
Ball (NOP) makes marginal contact with Gobert (UTA) during the rebound and does not affect his ability to get to the loose ball.
Ingram (NOP) makes contact to Mitchell's (UTA) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Ingram (NOP) initiates marginal contact with O'Neale (UTA) during the drive.
O'Neale (UTA) moves laterally into Ingram (NOP) and initiates contact that affects his SQBR.
Ball (NOP) maintains a legal guarding position on Conley (UTA) on the perimeter and any contact when he moves alongside of his path during the drive to the basket is incidental.
Gobert (UTA) and Ingram (NOP) make incidental contact with each other as they go for the rebound.

Holiday (NOP) maintains a legal guarding position on Mitchell (UTA) on the perimeter.  Holiday then makes marginal contact with Mitchell when he gathers the ball at the end of his drive that does not affect his SQBR.
Favors (NOP) makes contact to Gobert's (UTA) arm that affects his dunk attempt.
Ball (NOP) sets the screen on Ingles (UTA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
